Title: The Ontological Aspects of COTEM  
Author: NRIA CASTELL 
Address: Campus Nord Mdul C5 Jordi Girona Salgado, 1-3 08034 Barcelona SPAIN  
Affiliation: Departament de Llenguatges i Sistemes Informtics Universitat Politcnica de Catalunya  
Abstract: This paper focusses on the problem of text processing for the task of updating a knowledge base, and on how the knowledge is organised using ontological criteria. The main issues addressed are the kind of knowledge needed for extracting facts conveyed in narrative texts as well as the design of a procedure to perform the parsing process independently of the domain. Our approach is based on categorizing texts from two points of view, one structural, related to the surface organization of the text, and the other conceptual, related to the domain onotlogy. Temporal information is a relevant source of information in narratives and therefore we focus on this problem proposing a representation to handle temporal units explicitly and to include a time ontology. We have designed a system for understanding news and we describe COTEM, the implemented prototype operating in a financial domain, paying special attention to knowledge representation. 
